There's no doubt that some lets say ....temporary, seasonal type of immigration is required by most countries; and these people will be on temporary work visas - not citizenship - and their rights aren't the same as citizens (this is an arrangement I have regularly been on myself during my travels ). But permanent immigration (with passports etc ) in a country which is already over populated, has its own working unemployment probkems, and limited space in housing, educations , health care is going to have many negative effects for that country. Some countries like Sweden & Germany , for eg, have different demographics - and probably need extra permanent residents). One also need to look at the culture & religion of the migrants becos some types will fit-in better to the host country than other types (this isn't racist - it's an absolute fact). Incidentally, I'm not suggesting we shouldn't help & support migrants - we should - but there are ways to do this other immediately going the route of permanent citizenship



